# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SSH Admin — Server Configuration
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Copy this file to .env and edit it with your servers.
# Servers defined here are automatically registered at startup.
# Duplicate servers (same host+user+port) are silently skipped.
#
# Format:
#   SSHADMIN_SERVER_<n>=name|user@host:port|key_path
#
# - port defaults to 22 if omitted (user@host)
# - key_path is optional (leave empty to use default ~/.ssh/ keys)
#
# Examples:
#   SSHADMIN_SERVER_1=staging|ubuntu@staging.example.com|~/.ssh/my-key.pem
#   SSHADMIN_SERVER_2=production|deploy@prod.example.com:22|
#   SSHADMIN_SERVER_3=bastion|admin@10.0.0.1:2222|~/.ssh/bastion_rsa
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# SSHADMIN_SERVER_1=my-server|user@host.example.com|~/.ssh/id_rsa
